# Cloudflare Pages configuration
#
# ── _redirects ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Single Page App — every URL that doesn't match a static file or a route
# folder we pre-render must fall through to the SPA shell. Pre-rendered
# route folders (dist/<route>/index.html) take precedence because they're
# matched first as static files; this block is the safety net for any
# new route that hasn't been pre-rendered yet (e.g. /blog/<new-slug>).
#
# CRITICAL: Cloudflare Pages automatically issues a 308 redirect to add
# trailing slashes to URLs that match a directory containing index.html
# (e.g. /blog → /blog/). This happens BEFORE _redirects rules are
# processed, so we cannot use _redirects to strip the slash — that would
# create a redirect loop. Instead, the canonical URL in each prerendered
# page's <link rel="canonical"> tag uses the trailing-slash form to match
# what Cloudflare actually serves. The non-slash URL is still in the
# sitemap and llms.txt; both versions resolve to the same content.
#
# We also redirect the legacy /signup path to /auth?next=/signup so old
# links still work, and the /billing path that the docs mention to the
# real /dashboard page (where the top-up button actually lives).

# 301 redirects first (they match before the SPA fallback)
/signup   /auth?next=/signup   301
/billing  /dashboard            301
/blog/:slug.md  /blog/:slug    301

# Pages Functions (live in functions/api/*.ts) are matched BEFORE _redirects.
# The /api/playground endpoint is a Cloudflare Pages Function — no _redirects
# entry needed. The SPA fallback below will not catch /api/* because CF
# Pages Functions match first.

# SPA fallback: anything that didn't match a static file → index.html.
/*    /index.html   200
